text: Leskovac (Serbian Cyrillic: Лесковац, ) is a city in southern Serbia. It is the administrative center of the Jablanica District. According to the 2011 census, the city has population of 60,288. The administrative area has a population of 144,206. ==Images== |Leskovac File:FLAG Leskovac.gif File:Srednji grb.jpg ==Other websites== Category:Cities in Serbia
